The National Examinations Council (NECO) has postponed the 2019 National Common Entrance Examination into unity schools to 27 April, 2019. A statement from NECO’s head of informal and public relations, Azeez Sani, said the examination which was initially scheduled for 13 April, was re-scheduled to give states with low registration of candidates the opportunity to register for the examination. He said a total of 70,720 candidates have so far registered for the examination. Candidates are however advised to download the new Examination Time-Table from the council’s website. NECO postpones national entrance exam into unity schools NECO postpones national common entrance examination, sets April 27 as new date NECO releases common entrance exams result